---
alwaysApply: true
---

Purpose

Prevent avatar/name inconsistencies across the application by enforcing a single identity source of truth and a strict avatar resolution order.

This rule exists because previous implementations caused:

Team page showing fallback initials instead of avatar

Different pages showing different avatars for the same user

member.avatar_url === null incorrectly overriding profile avatars

Duplicate identity rendering

This rule is locked and must not be changed without explicit approval.

1. Canonical Identity Key

The only valid identity key across the system is:

user_id

Mapping:

auth.users.id
= profiles.user_id
= member_submissions.user_id

Never use:

profiles.id
member_submissions.id
team_members.id

These are row identifiers, not identity identifiers.

2. Avatar Source of Truth

The single source of truth for avatars is:

profiles.avatar_url

Avatar resolution order must always be:

1️⃣ profiles.avatar_url
2️⃣ member_submissions.avatar_url (legacy fallback only)
3️⃣ fallback initials

Important rule:

member.avatar_url === null MUST NOT override profile.avatar_url

This bug previously caused owner avatars to disappear.

3. Avatar Cache Busting (MANDATORY)

All avatar URLs must include a cache-busting version parameter.

?v=<profiles.updated_at>

Example:

https://supabase.../avatars/<user_id>/avatar.png?v=2026-03-10T00:17:00

This prevents browser caching after avatar updates.

Cache busting must be applied inside the profile resolver, not in UI components.

4. Avatar Rendering Rule

All UI components must receive avatars from the resolver layer.

UI components must never fetch profile data directly.

Allowed:

resolveDisplayProfile()
resolveMembersDisplay()
resolveCurrentUserDisplay()

Forbidden:

auth.user.avatar_url
member.avatar_url
email-based fallback

All avatar data must come from the profile resolver pipeline.

5. Resolver Responsibilities

profile-resolver.ts is the single authority for identity display data.

It must output:

{
  id
  user_id
  name
  avatarUrl
}

UI components must treat this object as fully resolved display data.

No additional avatar logic should exist in UI.

6. Owner Row Special Case

Owner rows created in:

member_submissions

may contain:

avatar_url = null

This is expected and must not suppress profile avatars.

Resolver must always check:

profile.avatarUrl first
7. UI Component Rule

Components such as:

TeamSection
RotationSection
ScheduleView
MemberDashboard
TopNav

must render avatars only via:

<MemberAvatar avatarUrl={resolved.avatarUrl} />

UI components must never construct avatar URLs themselves.

8. Debug Logging (Development Only)

In development mode, resolvers should log identity resolution:

NODE_ENV === development

Log:

member.id
member.user_id
resolved.name
resolved.avatarUrl

This prevents silent identity mismatches.

9. Identity Consistency Requirement

For the same user_id, the following must always match:

Page	Avatar	Name
Top Nav	same	same
Account	same	same
Team	same	same
Rotation	same	same
Schedule	same	same

If any page differs, the resolver pipeline is broken.

10. Change Control

Do NOT modify avatar logic without reviewing:

profile-resolver.ts
resolveMembersDisplay()
resolveDisplayProfile()
resolveCurrentUserDisplay()

Any change must guarantee:

profiles.avatar_url remains the primary source
Final Rule
All avatars in Parallel MUST originate from profiles.avatar_url
and pass through profile-resolver.ts before reaching the UI.

No exceptions.
